Get data from IntChron

Source: R/intchron.R
intchron.Rd

IntChron is an indexing service for chronological data from multiple sources. This function queries IntChron to retrieve data from the specified database ('host'), countries and sites.

intchron(hosts, countries = NA, sites = NA, tabulate = TRUE)

intchron_hosts()

Arguments

hosts

Databases to be retrieved. See details.
countries

Vector of countries to be retrieved. See details.
sites

Vector of sites to be retrieved. See details.
tabulate

If TRUE (the default), the data retrieved will be combined into a data frame. Set FALSE to get the raw data from IntChron.

Value

At least hosts must be specified. Use intchron_hosts() to get a list of currently available hosts, or "all" to retrieve data from any database.

A data frame, or if tabulate = FALSE, a list of IntChron responses.

Details

See vignette("intchron").

Examples

# List available databases
intchron_hosts()

#>       host                             database
#> 1  egyptdb        Egyptian Radiocarbon Database
#> 2 intimate                    INTIMATE Database
#> 3     nrcf   NERC Radiocarbon Facility (Oxford)
#> 4      oxa  Oxford Radiocarbon Accelerator Unit
#> 5     sadb Southern Africa Radiocarbon Database

# Get all data from Jordan
intchron("all", countries = "Jordan")
